content.description:
Zit Slab is the first crack system left of the three Deception Cracks.  Start in a corner with jams and face moves to a small ledge.  Launch up the upper crack with great jams and huge buckets to the cliff top. 

  Possibly the best route of it's grade at West Elden. 

  Descent - Rap from anchors atop the Right Deception Crack or scramble down 4th class terrain to the right of PMC.
content.protection: .5 - 3.5 Camalots   Medium to Large Stoppers   Slings and Draws

content.description:
Verse in Ragtime climbs the arete 20' right of Five Easy Pieces.  Face climb past two bolts up the arete using huecos and crimps to a large ledge.  Belay off gear (1-2") or a tree at the top. 

  Descent - Scramble down 4th class terrain to the right or rap from two bolts at the top of the right deception crack.
content.protection: Two draws   Small stoppers and one very large cam are optional.

content.description:
TT's Terror starts in a finger crack with a tree growing out of it just left of Zit Slab's start. Climb the finger crack, trying not to step on the tree, to a nice crack in the upper headwall. Climb past awkward and difficult moves (possibly 5.9) through a pod to a nice hand crack.

 Descent - Rap from anchors atop the Right Deception Crack or scramble down 4th class terrain right of PMC.
content.protection: 1 x 0 TCU (Purple Metolius) This is the only gear that I could find to protect the crux.   1 set TCU's   .5 - 3 Camalots   Small, Medium, and Large Stoppers

content.description:
The Spread Flake is the right facing corner next to the Baxter Crack.   

  Climb the corner using jams, stems, and face holds to a large tree at the clif top.  Keep your eyes open for stem options on the way up.
content.protection:
Half Set Stoppers   1 set TCUs   .5 to #2 Camalot 

  Large Tree to anchor onto at top of route. 

  This route is typically TRed.  The gear is "there" but can be tricky to place and tends to take up the best jams and holds.
content.location: Located about 50 yards left (north) of the Deception Cracks, the Spread Flake climbs a large right facing corner.

content.description: Start on Spread Flake up to the ledge and move onto the left face asap and climb the face and arete.  Not much pro besides the fixed pin if it is still there.
content.protection: Pro is minimal.  I left a fixed pin on the FA.  Don't know if it is still there.
content.location: This route is a variation to Spread Flake on the left face and arete.

climbs.name: Right Elephant Crack
climbs.fa: TR: Phil Gleason, mid-60's  Lead: Paul Davidson, Kim Spence, ~1978

content.description:
This route is located about 20 yards left (north) of the Baxter Crack and the Spread Flake. 

  The Right Elephant Crack climbs a short but steep head wall.  Scramble up an easy but slick slab to the crack's start.  Big moves off jams and face holds take you through the crack to the cliff top.
content.protection:
.5 - #1 Camalot   Half Set Stoppers   Draws 

  Large tree about 20' back from the rim to rappel from.

content.description:
The Right Deception Crack is possibly the most climbed route at West Elden.  This route lies in a left facing corner to the left of Five Easy Pieces and Megadeath.  Climb an easy slab to access the corner.  Liebacks and jams lead to the clifftop.   

  Descent - Rappel from a two bolt anchor.
content.protection: 1-3" cams   Medium to Large Stoppers   Slings and draws

content.description: The obvious overhanging hand crack just right of John's Jugs.  Finishes off with an awkward wide crack move or two.  Similar to Twilight Zone in that the jams are locker but it's steeper and the exit is harder than the Zone.
content.protection: Leave the cams on the ground and climb it with hexes.  You can hang a truck on the placements you'll get in the spots where the pods open and close.

content.description:
The Prow starts by climbing out the left hand wall of a shallow cave to a nice stance below the steep headwall.  Climb the fingers to hands crack to the rim.  Make a gear anchor (Red and Gold Camalot size) or run the rope way back to the trees. 

  This is my favorite 5.9 at West Elden.
content.protection: 1 set stoppers   1 x #0 TCU (Purple Metolius)   1-2 x #1 TCU (Blue Metolius)   1-2 x #2 TCU (Yellow Metolius)   Doubles Purple through Gold Camalot
content.location: The Prow is about 40 yards north (Left) of the Deception Cracks.  The route is very easy to walk right by.  Keep an eye out for a large cave.  The route climbs out the left side of this cave.

content.description:
Sharing the same start with Verse in Ragtime, PMC climbs an off-width crack to a split.  The right hand finish climbs an easy wide crack to the top.  The left hand variation checks in at about 5.6 consisting of a nice hand crack. 

  Belay from gear (1-2") or from a tree. 

  Descent - Scramble down 4th class terrain to the right or rap from anchors atop the right hand deception crack.
content.protection: 2-4" cams   A few medium to large stoppers are optional.

content.description: Place a directional in the crack, then reach high for the first clip. Climb up crack to a stance, then stretch right for some pockets to establish yourself on the overhanging, colorful face - the crux. Continue up, then right to the arete, then up again. Round the arete and finish up slabby terrain. For a more difficult start, stick clip the second bolt and climb straight up small edges and dyno for the rounded ledge - 12+.        "Instead of hiding our heads in a prayer cloth and building walls against temptation, why not get better at fulfilling desire? Salvation is for the feeble, that's what I think." - Tom Robbins(Jitterbug Perfume).
content.protection: Bolts to anchor. A directional in the crack will keep the rope out of your way as you move onto the face.
content.location: 100 feet left of Deceptions, one buttress left of Gone Fishin.

content.description:
This route is the first crack system left of the Right Deception.  Climb an easy slab to the crux.  Face climbing, body English, and levitation get you to a small pod.  From this point it is mostly hands and fingers to the top.   

  The crux is awkward and difficult to protect.  Most folks TR this route. 

  Descent - Rappel from two bolts atop the Right Deception Crack or scramble down to the right of PMC.
content.protection: 1-3.5" Cams   Medium - Large Stoppers    Slings and Draws

content.description:
Megadeath shares the same start with Five Easy Pieces (FEP).  When FEP cuts up and right Megadeath climbs a nice hands crack to a small ledge.  From here layback around the overhang to a nice stance.  Then launch up hands to ow crack making a great left reach to the clifftop just as the climbing gets really hard. 

  Descent - Scramble down 4th class terrain right of PMC or rap from bolts atop the Right Deception Crack.
content.protection: 1-4" cams   Medium - Large Stoppers   Slings and Draws   Tape for your hands is not a bad idea.  My gobis took two weeks to heal.

content.description: Located just left of the Middle Deception.  Climb an easy slab to access the hands, fist and ow crack.  Fun moderate climbing leads to the cliff top. A #3 Camalot and and decent sized tree provide a belay on top. Rap Right Deception.
content.protection: 1-4" cams   Medium to Large Stoppers   Slings and Draws

content.description:
One of the best routes at West Elden, if you can climb it! 

  Located just right of the Baxter Crack, John's Jugs climbs the steep fingers and tips crack that splits an overhanging headwall. 

  Start over boulders and broken rock to access the crack.  Launch up the fingers/tips crack which widens to thin hands just before the cliff top.
content.protection:
2 x #0 TCU/Blue Alien   2 x #1 TCU/Green Alien   1 x #2 TCU/Yellow Alien   1 x .5 Camalot   1 x .75 Camalot   1 x 1 Camalot   Possibly a couple of stoppers   Draws 

  There are several sturdy trees at the top of this route for TR anchors or to rap off.  This route is easily TRed after climbing the Baxter Crack.
content.location: Located about 50 yards left (north) of the Deception Cracks.

climbs.name: Inferno
climbs.fa: Ross Hardwick, Larry Coats, Dugald Bremner (late 70's)

content.description:
Inferno is about 50' north (climbers left) of TT's Terror.  Start up a short slot which leads to an unprotected right traverse into a low angle left facing corner.  Run up the corner to a ledge below the left facing dihedral that makes up the business of Inferno.  Jam and stem up this corner to the cliff top.  The gear through the crux is difficult to place.  

  Descent - Rap from the anchors atop the Right Deception Crack or scramble down 4th class terrain right of PMC.
content.protection: 1 set TCU's   .5 - 4 Camalots   Medium Stoppers   Slings and Draws

content.description: Stem between loafs, then smear up a slab to a left facing dihedral with gear. Top out the dihedral onto a perch below the pretty, steep juggy face. Climb the featured face, crux, to an anchor near the top.
content.protection: Small cam or two and quick draws.
content.location: Between the Deceptions and the Prow.

content.description:
From the base of the Right Deception Crack climb up and right to a large corner.  Climb face and cracks just right of the corner to the cliff top. 

  This route is a great way to access the cliff top.
content.protection: Stoppers and a few cams.
content.location:
Five Easy Pieces is just right of the three Deception Cracks near the right hand end of Uptown. 

  Descent is by rappel from a two bolt anchor atop the Right Deception or by scrambling down 4th class terrain to right of PMC.

content.description: I'm adding this route because some people have asked me about it in the past.  It is a short little thing and was quite scary to lead on the FA. My guess is that it is 5.11.  It is a pretty little face but too tall for a highball so I lead it.
content.protection: Pro is tiny wires in the seam and when I did the FA I used a knife blade piton in the middle of the seam.  The drilled pro near the top turned out to be unnecessary since the move above was only about 5.7 but I put this up ground up and didn't know what was coming.  That's why I called it Chicken Fixin's.
content.location: This route is on the far N end of Uptown on a small S. facing face. It can be recognized by a left slanting seem on the flat face.  There is a drilled baby angle on the bulge near the top.  (or there was 30 years ago when I did the FA)

content.description: Start ten feet right of the initially dirty, mossy crack system, on a flake jug on the face. Climb good, slabby features left and up to the crack system previously mentioned. Climb a few moves up the low angle wide crack(beware of your rope falling into a slot just above), then angle slightly left up the slabby dihedral with a seam that offers some protection just before a ledge is encountered on your left. Use the ledge, or not, and continue up the crack line that leads to the steep, striking prow/arete with the handrail that curves along it's edge - the business. To the first bolt the route is about 5.7 with sparse gear. Climb up the steep, juggy handrail past two more bolts to a sinker pocket and well hidden chain anchor at the lip. Don't cheat yourself by climbing to the steep lip of the cliff, clipping and lowering. Top it out for old school satisfaction, then reverse the topout moves and lower.         *This climb was established entirely on lead.
content.protection: #2 camalot, #.75 camalot, 5 quick draws. 60m rope.
content.location: Bold is Love is located about 50 feet to the right of The Prow. Eyeball the handrail high above, and the line to it will be fairly obvious. Be sure to avoid the mossy crack in the first twenty feet by starting up the face to the right. The first hold is a big, angling jug.

content.description:
The Baxter Crack is located about 50 yards north of the Deception Cracks.  Pass through the tunnel boulder and look up.  The Spread Flake is the right facing corner.  The Baxter crack is the left facing corner.   

  Scramble up and over boulders and then up a lower angle slab with a crack.  When the wall steepens head take one of two options.  1. Climb up and right through a wide crack to the cliff top.  2.  Climb straight up a sweet #2 Camalot crack to the cliff top.  Option #1 is probably in the 5.6 range.  Option #2 could be as hard as 5.8+, but is very high quality climbing.
content.protection: .5 - #2 Camalots   Half set Stoppers   Draws   Rap from the tree atop the Spread Flake (Right facing corner 15' left of Baxter Crack.)

content.description: A few years ago Dean and I TRed the arete between Zit Slab and the Left Deception.  It checks in at about 5.10a or so.  Starts on the arete then quickly moves right up plates, flexable flakes, and jugs to the top.
content.protection: Top Rope Only!  Please do not bolt this route.
content.location: Arete between Zit Slab and Left Deception.

content.description: Area north of the barbwire fence.
